    "text": "I can see your data, including the score itself: your recovery score is 81% today, with high confidence. Recovery scores are built from your overnight physiology — mainly heart-rate variability, resting heart rate, and sleep — each compared against your own recent history rather than population tables. Today's inputs explain the number: your HRV of 61 ms is about 2 ms above your 30-day baseline of 59 ms; your resting heart rate of 55 bpm is about 1 bpm below its 30-day baseline of 56 bpm; and you slept 7.5 h, right on your 7.4 h need. Small nudges in the right direction on all three inputs add up to a green-leaning score — the label is earned by those comparisons, not by a generic threshold.",
